{"lemma":"كَفَّيْ","slug":"كَفَّيْ","root":"ك.ف.ف","root_slug":"ك-ف-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ف-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَفَّيْ","root":"كفف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43077"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to desist or to cease","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَنْ أَنَامَ حَتَّى يَكُفَّ ٱلطِّفْلُ عَنِ ٱلْبُكَاءِ.","english":"I will not sleep until the child stops crying."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hem, to skirt","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to curb, to contain, to constrict","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hinder, to keep somebody off from something","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَهُوَ ٱلَّذِى كَفَّ أَيْدِيَهُمْ عَنكُمْ وَأَيْدِيَكُمْ عَنْهُم بِبَطْنِ مَكَّةَ مِنۢ بَعْدِ أَنْ أَظْفَرَكُمْ عَلَيْهِمْ ۚ وَكَانَ ٱللَّهُ بِمَا تَعْمَلُونَ بَصِيرًا","english":"And it is He who withheld their hands from you and your hands from them within [the area of] Makkah after He caused you to overcome them. And ever is Allāh, of what you do, Seeing."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"palm of the hand, the inner surface of the hand from wrist to finger tips","examples":[{"text":"وَأُحِيطَ بِثَمَرِهِ فَأَصْبَحَ يُقَلِّبُ كَفَّيْهِ عَلَىٰ مَا أَنفَقَ فِيهَا وَهِيَ خَاوِيَةٌ عَلَىٰ عُرُوشِهَا وَيَقُولُ يَا لَيْتَنِي لَمْ أُشْرِكْ بِرَبِّي أَحَدًا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paw, foot, claw"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handful"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scale (balance)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glove"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"quire"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bar (of candy)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَفَّ (kaffa) (form I) – abstaining, abstention, cessation, desistance, discontinuation, refraining, stoppage, suspension","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *kapp-. Cognate with Hebrew כף (kaf)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43077","headword_ar":"كَفَى","root":"kfY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, sufficed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contented:"},{"kind":"text","text":"hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaAniY fulaAnN AlA^amora","text_ar":"كَفَانِى فُلَانٌ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one sufficed me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contented me, in respect of the affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., by taking upon himself to perform it or accomplish it if good, or to prevent it or avert it if evil: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaAniY $ahiydFA","text_ar":"كَفَانِى شَهِيدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sufficed me as,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, a witness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he suffices me as,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, such:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundantly prefixed to its agent, and sometimes to its objective complement; as in exs. cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":". See Ham, p. 152."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY","text_ar":"كَفَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It sufficed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it stood instead of another thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) [as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY Eano gayorihi","text_ar":"كَفَى عَنْ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY binaA","text_ar":"كَفَى بِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaAnaA","text_ar":"كَفَانَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. See W, pp. 5 and 6 ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY","text_ar":"كَفَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakofiY","text_ar":"يَكْفِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kifaAyapN","text_ar":"كِفَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa","text_ar":"دَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa","text_ar":"مَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har, p. 43, q. v.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaAhu Al$~ar~a","text_ar":"كَفَاهُ الشَّرَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repelled from him evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he defended him therefrom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he freed him therefrom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of God, and of a man, &c.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}